Jersey Club is a raw high energy, cultivated by the youth of Newark, New Jersey. It has over 20 years of success with music and dance. The dancing was cultivated by “The Brick City Dancers” and “EnVy Dance Group.” The dance style features local party dances like the Percolator, Lock it Up/ Stolen Car, One Leg Get Back, Rock Ya Hips, and intricate choreography from the local dancers and dance teams/groups. The music side has been cultivated by the Legendary DJ Tameil and the Super Group of Producers, “The Brick Bandits.” The power of Jersey Club is currently being displayed by popular music artists today, like Drake, Lil Uzi Vert and Coileray, to name a few. Your presenter, Anthony “Solo”  Harris, was a part of the Legendary EnVy dance group and is considered a Jersey Club Historian. With his 20 years of experience, he is equipped to show the youth the power of unity, networking and how working together with your fellow brothers and sisters can achieve greatness while having fun. Anthony looks forward to mentoring and guiding you if you have an interest in music, dance and cultural empowerment.

When the universe picks you its never by accident. Im honored to be apart of some historical moments within Jersey Club. Thank you @djtameil 🐐 & @dj_tim_dolla 🐐 (RIP) A special shouts out to Dj Sega, Rod Lee & Dj A-Plus. The "Curtis" mixtape will forever be a special 💎 to me personally. 

#3 Clockwork & #15 Partytime produced by yours truly 🔊🎵🔊

* First professional Melanated street dancers from New Jersey to be on the Internet. 2003

* First to put Jersey club music and dancing on the Internet by way of urbanvision.net, before YouTube, before MySpace. 2003

*First to create a dance mixtape (VHS/DVD)in New Jersey with a Jersey Club soundtrack by Michael Williams 2003/2004

* First dancers to create 2 full length jersey club CDs hosted by Legendary DeeJay Ran. 2004/2005

* First dancers to have their jersey club songs featured on a Jersey Club album produced by the Legendary DJ Tameil Paynes and  DeeJay Tim Dolla 2006.

* First dancers to travel out of New Jersey to perform personalized Jersey Club performances at HBCUs around the country in the early 2003-2008

* First performers to open the Prudential Center 2007

* First to sell out Newark Symphony Hall ‘s Terrance ballroom twice with their Dance Warz Competition. 2006/2007
Attracting infinite abundance has brought me more peace than chasing fame.

I’m extremely grateful for my journey, as I know it has led me to my purpose and current missions. Twenty years ago, my brothers and I embarked on a dance journey from Newark, NJ, setting a standard for the young artists growing up in our community. They could see us develop and achieve success as dancers and music producers in real time. We were the first DANCERS to create Jersey Club CDs, secure sponsorship deals (thanks to @deejayran ), and travel across the country representing New Jersey. As I reflect on our 20-year anniversary and observe what is happening now, I can truly see that the universe had a plan not only for us but for the entire community. I am grateful for the role we played in its foundational growth.
